1
00:00:02,211 --> 00:00:04,671
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:27,588
Greetings to all of you at the ICPO.

3
00:01:27,671 --> 00:01:29,131
I am L.

4
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:31,925
Whether the guilty party
is an individual or a group,

5
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,094
there's a strong possibility
that they are Japanese.

6
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:37,431
Kira, I've got a pretty good idea
what your motivation might be,

7
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:39,933
and I can guess what you hope to achieve.

8
00:01:40,017 --> 00:01:41,143
However…

9
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:44,187
what you're doing right now is evil.

10
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:45,814
[Light] You… you bastard.

11
00:01:46,148 --> 00:01:47,399
[L] Now… try to kill me!

12
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:49,276
-I am justice!
-What the hell is going on?

13
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,278
I protect the innocent
and those who fear evil!

14
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:54,197
I'm the one who will become the god
of a new world that everyone desires!

15
00:01:54,323 --> 00:01:55,532
L…

16
00:01:55,866 --> 00:01:56,783
Kira…

17
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:59,244
[Kira and Light] I will hunt you down
wherever you're hiding,

18
00:01:59,328 --> 00:02:00,287
and I will eliminate you!

19
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:01,288
I am…

20
00:02:01,413 --> 00:02:02,289
I am…

21
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:04,166
[Kira and L] … justice!

22
00:02:04,291 --> 00:02:07,210
DEALINGS

23
00:02:07,429 --> 00:02:09,858
[car horns honking]

24
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:11,214
SERIAL MURDER
SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS HQ

25
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:12,966
[Yagami] All right. Let's start
with the tip line reports.

26
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:13,967
[detective 1] Yes, sir.

27
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:17,304
Up to this point, we've received
3029 responses about the murders

28
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:18,847
via telephone and e-mail.

29
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:21,680
Most of these have been curious citizens
and prank calls,

30
00:02:21,755 --> 00:02:26,435
but there are 14 people who claimed
to either know Kira or who have seen him.

31
00:02:27,731 --> 00:02:30,901
All 14 accounts were followed up on
and carefully documented.

32
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:33,528
However, nobody could provide
any information

33
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:35,405
that wasn't already publicly available.

34
00:02:36,323 --> 00:02:39,826
And lastly, this week
there were additional 21 people

35
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,870
who called in claiming to be Kira.

36
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:42,996
[indistinct chatter]

37
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,415
Hm… [clears throat]

38
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,335
[detective 1] We didn't want
to rule anything out.

39
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:52,547
So, we followed standard procedure
and created files for all 21 of them.

40
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:55,842
[Yagami] Uh huh. All right.
On to the victim reports.

41
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:56,927
[detective 2] Yes, sir.

42
00:02:58,387 --> 00:03:00,138
Upon further investigation,

43
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:03,725
we have confirmed that information
of the heart attack victims

44
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:08,063
was in fact publicly available in Japan
immediately prior to their deaths.

45
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:10,357
Also,

46
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:14,986
concerning L's request that we investigate
the time of death for each victim,

47
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,655
we found that all of them occurred

48
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:20,617
between the hours of 4 p.m. and 2 a.m.
on weekdays, local time,

49
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:24,204
with 68 percent of them
occurring between 8 p.m. and 12 a.m.

50
00:03:24,538 --> 00:03:27,290
Weekends and holidays appeared
to be the exception to this rule

51
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:30,085
as the times of deaths vary
much more widely than during the week.

52
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:32,254
[L through voice modifier]
That information

53
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:33,672
is extremely relevant for us.

54
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:36,216
It suggests that,
given the times of death,

55
00:03:36,717 --> 00:03:39,636
our suspect could very well be a student.

56
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,138
Hmm?

57
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:44,099
[L] Based on the fact
that Kira is only killing criminals,

58
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,559
I think it's safe to assume

59
00:03:45,684 --> 00:03:48,562
that he is driven
by a very idealistic notion of justice.

60
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:52,649
It's highly possible he may even aspire
to be some sort of godlike figure.

61
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,192
We're dealing with an individual

62
00:03:54,276 --> 00:03:56,820
who has a very childish concept
of right and wrong.

63
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,156
[muttering]

64
00:03:59,281 --> 00:04:01,491
[L] Of course,
this is mere speculation at this point,

65
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:04,244
but still, I recommend you re-examine
any assumptions you've made

66
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,997
as to whether or not our suspect
could be a student.

67
00:04:07,456 --> 00:04:09,499
We must consider every possibility.

68
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,878
I believe that's the shortest route
to finding and arresting Kira.

69
00:04:13,545 --> 00:04:15,255
Please, continue with your report.

70
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,924
Hm. All right.

71
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:20,886
Does anyone else have
something they'd like to add?

72
00:04:21,511 --> 00:04:22,637
Um, yes sir.

73
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,389
[Yagami] What is it, Matsuda?

74
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:28,393
Um… well, I'm not saying this
to support Kira

75
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:30,812
or to condone the murders, but…

76
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:33,148
in the last few days throughout the world,

77
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,233
but especially here in Japan,

78
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:39,196
we've observed the dramatic decrease
in the number of violent crimes committed.

79
00:04:39,488 --> 00:04:42,073
[muttering]

80
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,743
[Yagami] Well, I suppose it makes sense.

81
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:47,329
We've suspected
something like that would happen.

82
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:48,580
Anything else?

83
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:50,081
No.

84
00:04:50,551 --> 00:04:52,579
[unsettling music playing]

85
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:55,629
[Yagami] Well, that about sums up
our report for today. L?

86
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,422
[L] Thank you, everyone.

87
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:59,674
I feel we're one step closer
to finding Kira.

88
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:03,470
Before I go, I'm afraid I have
one additional request to make.

89
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:06,389
This is directed
to the teams investigating the victims,

90
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:08,058
TV news, and internet.

91
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,601
I would like you to go back

92
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,436
and take a closer look at the exact way

93
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,939
in which the victims' identities
were made public.

94
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,398
Be as thorough as possible.

95
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:18,360
[L] In particular,
I want to know if photos of the victims

96
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:20,779
were made available to the public
in Japan.

97
00:05:20,904 --> 00:05:22,697
[through voice modifier]
I leave it to you.

98
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:25,158
[groaning]

99
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:27,035
-[Matsuda] Chief!
-Hm?

100
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:29,621
You look like you could use one of these.
Sleepy much?

101
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:31,915
Ah. Thank you. That'll do the trick.

102
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:34,751
I feel all these late nights
are starting to take their toll.

103
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:37,212
[Yagami gulps] Ah.

104
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:40,340
About what I said earlier at our meeting…

105
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:43,885
Well, now that I think about it, um,
I'm sure everyone already knew that.

106
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:45,762
I wanted to apologize.

107
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:47,889
What on earth are you talking about?

108
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,766
Nobody said it'll be easy
to speak the truth,

109
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,101
but it has to be done.

110
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:53,728
Especially when it is something
that isn't easy to say.

111
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:55,689
Huh?

112
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:56,815
Having said that,

113
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:59,067
if you'd gone on to say
that we should commend Kira

114
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,903
for doing such a great job
of reducing violent crime,

115
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,531
then yes, I might have
had a little problem with that.

116
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:07,409
[Matsuda] Oh, no. No, I wouldn't.
That would never happen!

117
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:09,244
[Yagami laughing] Just kidding.

118
00:06:10,996 --> 00:06:12,747
[Sayu] I knew I can count on you, Light.

119
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:16,251
Hey, so do you think you're ready
to try a few on your own now?

120
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:17,335
Huh?

121
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:19,296
Yeah. I guess so.

122
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:20,589
[doorbell rings]

123
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:22,924
Oh, sounds like Dad's home.

124
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:26,261
-[Sachiko] Welcome home, dear.
-[Yagami] Thank you.

125
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:28,680
He's home really early today.

126
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:31,850
Hey, why don't you at least
try the last problem by yourself?

127
00:06:32,017 --> 00:06:34,519
[Sayu] I will, but maybe after dinner.

128
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:35,770
Yeah, right.

129
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:39,232
Helping your sister with her homework?

130
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:40,650
You sure are relaxed.

131
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:41,860
Of course.

132
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:43,653
If the police try to come after me,

133
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:46,781
I'm pretty confident I've got something
that'll give me the advantage.

134
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:50,660
Hey, glad you could join us for dinner.

135
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:51,995
You hungry, Dad?

136
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:54,289
Yeah. It's been a long day.

137
00:06:56,218 --> 00:06:58,346
[chopsticks clattering]

138
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,883
So, Light, tell me.
How are your studies going?

139
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:07,636
Hm? Everything's okay, I guess.

140
00:07:07,719 --> 00:07:09,804
Whatever. He's at the top of his class.

141
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,556
My big brother is a genius!

142
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,059
That's my son!
We're all proud of you, Light.

143
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:15,602
[Light] Is everything okay, Dad?

144
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:16,853
You look tired.

145
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:17,896
[Yagami] Yeah.

146
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:20,148
I'm not able to say too much about it,

147
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:23,360
but this case I'm working on now
is really tough.

148
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,654
[Ryuk] I see.

149
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:29,407
-Well, well. Daddy's a policeman.
-[keyboard clacking]

150
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,953
And that must be the reason
why you're so confident?

151
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:36,373
That's right. It's easy for me to hack
into Dad's computer.

152
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,666
We're on a home network,

153
00:07:37,749 --> 00:07:40,085
so I can copy the files I need
without leaving a trace.

154
00:07:40,835 --> 00:07:42,963
This way, I can keep track
of their investigation.

155
00:07:44,339 --> 00:07:45,256
Here we go.

156
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,814
Well, isn't that interesting?

157
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:04,025
Looks like the police are already
beginning to suspect a student.

158
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:05,402
[Ryuk cackles]

159
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,988
I guess that means you're in trouble.

160
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:09,614
Hm…

161
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:17,914
If the cause of death is written within
40 seconds of writing the person's name,

162
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:18,915
it will happen.

163
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,335
If the cause of death is not specified,

164
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,546
the person will simply
die of a heart attack.

165
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:26,631
After writing the cause of death,

166
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:30,260
details of the death should be written
in the next six minutes and 40 seconds.

167
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:31,761
That sound right to you, Ryuk?

168
00:08:32,387 --> 00:08:33,513
So, what's your point?

169
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:36,975
In other words, if I write
heart attacks as the cause of death,

170
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:38,893
then I should be able to write down

171
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:41,563
all the details including
time of death afterward, shouldn't I?

172
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:46,026
Looks like I will be able to provide you
with more entertainment now.

173
00:08:48,455 --> 00:08:50,683
[tense music playing]

174
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,166
[inmate grunts]

175
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:08,757
[panting]

176
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:11,799
-[grunting]
-[chuckles]

177
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:14,137
[grunts]

178
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,723
Inmate 148, what's wrong?

179
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:17,974
Snap out of it!

180
00:09:24,823 --> 00:09:26,983
[grunting, gasping]

181
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:30,070
[inmates] Huh?

182
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,657
TASK FORCE HEADQUARTERS

183
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:35,825
[Yagami] What?

184
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,994
I-- I don't believe this.

185
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:40,830
Another 23 victims yesterday?
Are these confirmed?

186
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:41,831
[detective] Yes.

187
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:45,251
The day before there were
another 23 victims.

188
00:09:45,627 --> 00:09:48,296
He's killing one off,
every hour on the hour.

189
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:51,966
Considering that this new pattern
has been going on for two weekdays…

190
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:55,428
It does punch some holes in the theory
that our suspect is a student.

191
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:58,348
Maybe not.
Anybody can skip two days of school.

192
00:09:58,473 --> 00:09:59,599
[L] You're missing the point.

193
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:01,142
-Huh?
-Huh?

194
00:10:01,226 --> 00:10:04,479
[L] It does appear less likely now
that Kira is a student,

195
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:07,649
but that's not the message he's sending
by doing this.

196
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:10,068
Ask yourselves, why every hour?

197
00:10:10,193 --> 00:10:11,861
And why are all these victims in prisons

198
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:13,988
where they are sure to be
discovered immediately?

199
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:16,032
Why not other criminals like before?

200
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,076
I believe Kira is telling us

201
00:10:18,243 --> 00:10:20,286
that not only can he kill from a distance,

202
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:23,248
but he can also
determine the time of death.

203
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:25,583
[muttering]

204
00:10:26,668 --> 00:10:28,795
[L] But something's not right.

205
00:10:29,195 --> 00:10:32,741
As soon as we began to suspect
that Kira might be a student,

206
00:10:33,258 --> 00:10:34,801
the pacing of the killings changed.

207
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:36,553
As if to contradict that theory.

208
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:37,804
Coincidence?

209
00:10:38,263 --> 00:10:39,264
No.

210
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:40,557
Too convenient.

211
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:45,478
This can only mean that Kira
has access to police information.

212
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:47,188
It's obvious now.

213
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:49,482
This is a direct challenge to me.

214
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:54,863
[Light] I'd say L is probably
starting to sweat a little by now.

215
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:56,781
What'll really make his job difficult

216
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,117
is that I've deliberately left
about 50 criminals alive

217
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,118
for times like this.

218
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,119
Oh?

219
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:03,163
If L is as good as they say,

220
00:11:03,246 --> 00:11:05,039
by now, he should be starting to suspect

221
00:11:05,123 --> 00:11:07,083
someone with connections to the police.

222
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,211
[L] So, Kira has found a way

223
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:13,756
to obtain information
from the Task Force headquarters.

224
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:16,134
This is one fact that cannot be ignored.

225
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:19,345
But what does he get out of all this?

226
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:22,348
What is he hoping to achieve in the end?

227
00:11:25,185 --> 00:11:26,686
There's one thing I don't get.

228
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:29,314
Showing them
you have connections to the police,

229
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:31,107
makes it easier for them to find you

230
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,359
than when they
just suspected you a student.

231
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,195
Well, my real agenda is…

232
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:39,115
to get close to L,
so I can eliminate him.

233
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:40,491
How are you gonna do that?

234
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,119
You still don't understand human beings.

235
00:11:43,203 --> 00:11:46,331
In this world, there are very few people
who actually trust each other.

236
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:48,917
And it's no different for the police,
you know.

237
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,753
What's especially important

238
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:54,797
is that L and the investigators
don't trust each other at all.

239
00:11:55,006 --> 00:11:55,924
Think about it.

240
00:11:56,007 --> 00:11:58,593
Could you trust someone
whose name and face you don't even know?

241
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,971
When L discovers that I'm somehow
getting confidential information,

242
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:04,599
he'll be obligated
to start investigating the police

243
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:06,184
to find the source of the leak.

244
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,102
When that happens,

245
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:11,731
it'll only be a matter of time
before the police start resenting L.

246
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,192
On the surface it will appear

247
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:17,612
that L and the investigation team
are working together to try to catch me.

248
00:12:18,196 --> 00:12:19,197
But in reality,

249
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:21,658
L will investigate the police,

250
00:12:21,783 --> 00:12:23,451
and they will be investigating L.

251
00:12:24,786 --> 00:12:26,704
I'm not the one who is going to find L.

252
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,374
I can let the police do that for me.

253
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:32,418
And when they do,
that's when I'll eliminate him.

254
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,272
TASK FORCE HEADQUARTERS

255
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:53,564
[Yagami] What's this about?

256
00:12:53,648 --> 00:12:55,525
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

257
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:57,860
[detective 1] With all due respect, Chief,
we're resigning.

258
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,404
[muttering]

259
00:12:59,529 --> 00:13:01,948
[detective 1] We demand that you assign us
to a different case.

260
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:04,450
Otherwise, you can have our badges
right here and now.

261
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:06,119
Why? You're good cops!

262
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:07,412
Isn't it clear?

263
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:09,664
It's because we value our lives, sir.

264
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:11,457
[detective 2] If what L says is true,

265
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:13,376
Kira has some ESP-like power

266
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:16,587
that somehow allows him to kill people
indirectly from anywhere.

267
00:13:16,671 --> 00:13:18,298
[detective 3] Well, if I were Kira, sir,

268
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:21,342
I'd probably wanna try and get rid
of the people who are trying to catch me.

269
00:13:21,426 --> 00:13:24,095
Let's face it, he knows he will be
sentenced to death if he's caught.

270
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,014
[detective 1] We all sat here and watched

271
00:13:26,097 --> 00:13:29,809
when L decided to pull that media stunt
and challenge Kira to kill him.

272
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,853
Well, it was all very impressive
at the time,

273
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:33,938
but then again,
L never had to show his face

274
00:13:34,022 --> 00:13:35,732
or reveal his name for that matter.

275
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:38,067
I'm sure you recall L's last request?

276
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:39,986
He asked that we take a closer look

277
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,071
at how these victims' identities
were made public

278
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:44,490
and specifically, to determine
whether photos of the victims

279
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:47,118
were available to the public
prior to their deaths.

280
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:49,954
Well, it turns out he was right!

281
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:52,373
Every single one of those victims'
names and photos

282
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:55,043
were broadcast to the Japanese public,
and then they died!

283
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:56,627
Unlike someone we know,

284
00:13:56,753 --> 00:13:58,421
we're out there investigating this case

285
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:01,132
wearing police IDs
with our names and photos on them!

286
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,551
Anybody with a computer
can find out who we are!

287
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,054
We don't hide our faces!
We're out in the open!

288
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:09,766
Sir, the truth is,
we could be killed by Kira at any time.

289
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,519
For these reasons,
we refuse to continue working this case.

290
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:15,229
Excuse us, Chief.

291
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,107
Hey, stop! All of you,

292
00:14:18,483 --> 00:14:19,776
hold it right there!

293
00:14:19,901 --> 00:14:20,943
[door closes]

294
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,240
Huh?

295
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:28,034
In order to solve this problem,

296
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,994
we must establish the concept

297
00:14:30,178 --> 00:14:32,764
that X squared equals large X.

298
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,707
Now pay attention
because this is important.

299
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:36,959
Before we tackle
more complex quadratic equations,

300
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:39,879
we have to start thinking
of large X's value

301
00:14:40,088 --> 00:14:42,507
as simply the multiple of two integers.

302
00:14:43,216 --> 00:14:45,927
Now, let's apply this concept
to our first problem.

303
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:52,809
[Watari] We brought the FBI to Japan
four days ago.

304
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:54,560
They are fully operational.

305
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:56,896
As requested, they're now
gathering intel on the police.

306
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:59,482
-[L] And this is the complete list?
-[Watari] Yes.

307
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:03,861
There are 141 people in the police force

308
00:15:03,945 --> 00:15:07,281
who have access to classified information
regarding the investigation.

309
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,617
I am sure that somewhere in this list

310
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:13,121
of the police officers
and the people closest to them,

311
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,873
we will find our suspect.

312
00:15:15,957 --> 00:15:17,208
SOICHIRO YAGAMI
DETECTIVE SUPERINTENDENT

313
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,090
NPA HEAD OF SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS
SERIAL MURDER CASE

314
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:22,422
[Ryuk] Light, you got a second?

315
00:15:23,131 --> 00:15:24,590
I've already told you, Ryuk.

316
00:15:24,674 --> 00:15:26,259
You can't talk to me in public.

317
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,177
How many times do I have to tell you?

318
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:30,805
In that case, I'll talk, you just listen.

319
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:33,641
If you don't want to hear me,
you can plug your ears or something.

320
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:36,978
First of all,
I don't have anything against you.

321
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:38,604
I actually think the notebook

322
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:40,523
couldn't have been picked up
by a better person.

323
00:15:41,107 --> 00:15:44,402
I'm here 'cause I have to stick around
till the Death Note is finished,

324
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,529
or I see you die, whichever comes first.

325
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,990
But make no mistake, Light,

326
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:51,284
I'm not on your side or L's side.

327
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,288
[Light] Yeah. Well,
I knew that much already.

328
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,123
You'll never hear me say anything

329
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:59,459
about whether what you're doing
is right or wrong.

330
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:02,295
I'm not here to support you
or give you my opinion.

331
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:03,880
I'm just a spectator,

332
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,256
but as your roommate,

333
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:07,425
I might have a few things to say
now and then.

334
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:09,343
What's this about, Ryuk?

335
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:11,679
Why are you
telling me all this stuff now, anyway?

336
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:13,389
It's really not like you.

337
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:17,477
It's just that I'm no ally of yours,
or Kira's, if you prefer.

338
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,270
The only reason I'm going to tell you this

339
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:21,856
is because, personally,
it is starting to creep me out.

340
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:23,483
[Light] Get to the point already.

341
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,568
[chuckles]

342
00:16:26,027 --> 00:16:28,362
You are being followed by another human.

343
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:29,697
He's watching you right now.

344
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:48,382
It's really starting to get on my nerves.

345
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:51,344
I realize there's no way he can see me,

346
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:55,056
but because I'm always following
behind you wherever you go,

347
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:57,600
I feel like I'm constantly being watched.

348
00:16:58,392 --> 00:16:59,810
[Light] That's a problem.

349
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,605
I'll have to get rid of him
as soon as possible.

350
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:07,818
Who would be following me?

351
00:17:07,944 --> 00:17:08,861
[door squeaks]

352
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:11,739
Does this mean L is already starting
to suspect the police?

353
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,160
If he's gonna investigate the police,

354
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:18,371
he'll need a lot of resources
and manpower.

355
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,874
Even if he has as many
as 50 people on the case,

356
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:24,669
I don't see how they could ever figure out
that I'm Kira.

357
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:28,506
I shouldn't look like anything other
than your average high school senior.

358
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,009
But the longer I let this person
keep following me,

359
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,887
the greater the chance
is they'll figure out who I really am.

360
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,181
Above all…

361
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:38,891
I need my stalker's name.

362
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,643
Once I figure that out,

363
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:42,895
I can get rid of him for good.

364
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,605
-[Ryuk] Light.
-[Light] Hm?

365
00:17:45,273 --> 00:17:47,483
[Ryuk] I'm gonna let you in
on a little secret.

366
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:51,279
What makes a Shinigami and a human
who has a Death Note different?

367
00:17:51,529 --> 00:17:53,197
Well, there are two things.

368
00:17:54,574 --> 00:17:56,075
And why do Shinigami

369
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:58,536
have to write the names of humans
in their Death Notes?

370
00:17:58,661 --> 00:17:59,787
You got any ideas?

371
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,248
Of course not. Why would I know that?

372
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:06,043
You know, you sure are talkative today.

373
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:10,006
It's because we are able
to take human lifespans for ourselves.

374
00:18:10,298 --> 00:18:12,592
Huh? Wait, what do you mean by that?

375
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:16,262
Let's say you have a human
who is due to live until the age of 60

376
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:19,557
and a God of Death wrote
that this person would die at 40.

377
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:23,060
Sixty minus 40 equals 20.

378
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:26,230
Now those 20 years
taken from someone in the human world

379
00:18:26,314 --> 00:18:28,649
are added to that God of Death's life.

380
00:18:28,983 --> 00:18:29,859
Huh.

381
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:32,612
So, it means that
as long as we don't slack off,

382
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:35,197
even if someone
was to shoot us in the head,

383
00:18:35,323 --> 00:18:37,325
or stab us in the heart with a knife,

384
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:39,035
a God of Death cannot die.

385
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:40,661
On the other hand,

386
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:43,623
no matter how many names
you write in your Death Note,

387
00:18:43,748 --> 00:18:45,750
your lifespan will not increase.

388
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,376
That is the first difference

389
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:50,463
between gods of death and humans
who possess a Death Note.

390
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:53,007
[chuckles] That's something
about Shinigami

391
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:54,550
that I haven't heard before.

392
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,594
Pretty interesting stuff.

393
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:58,763
The second difference between us

394
00:18:58,888 --> 00:19:01,223
will probably be
of even greater interest to you.

395
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:04,310
Though this has less to do
with lengthening life

396
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:06,270
and more to do with cutting it short.

397
00:19:06,354 --> 00:19:07,688
What do you mean cutting it short?

398
00:19:08,898 --> 00:19:12,526
Shinigami can tell what the person's name
is by just looking at their face.

399
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:14,028
We know instantly.

400
00:19:14,445 --> 00:19:16,197
And do you have any idea why?

401
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,866
Because through a Shinigami's eyes,

402
00:19:18,949 --> 00:19:21,452
a human's name
can be seen above their head.

403
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:22,578
Not only that,

404
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:24,622
we see their lifespan as well.

405
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:27,208
Their name and lifespan?

406
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,001
LIGHT YAGAMI

407
00:19:29,085 --> 00:19:31,968
[Ryuk] That's right. I'm able to see
your name and lifespan right now.

408
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,143
[tense music playing]

409
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:36,050
[Ryuk] If I converted that to human time,

410
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,469
I could tell you
how many years you've got left.

411
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,638
But there's no way I'd ever tell you that.

412
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:44,684
I may have a big mouth,
but even I wouldn't go that far.

413
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:46,644
[laughs]

414
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:50,523
Shinigami never have to worry
that they won't be able to kill a person

415
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:52,608
just because they don't know their name,

416
00:19:52,942 --> 00:19:54,694
and every time we do take a life,

417
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:57,905
we always know exactly how many years
we are going to receive.

418
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,700
Our eyes just aren't the same,

419
00:20:00,825 --> 00:20:03,285
and that is the difference
between you and I.

420
00:20:04,829 --> 00:20:06,080
However…

421
00:20:06,414 --> 00:20:10,209
if a Shinigami drops his Death Note
and a human picks it up,

422
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:13,087
he can grant that human
the eyes of a Shinigami,

423
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:16,132
but only if a deal is made,

424
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:18,759
one that has been with us
since ancient times.

425
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:20,136
And what's the deal?

426
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,806
The price for having the Shinigami's eyes…

427
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:28,853
is half of that person's
remaining lifespan.

428
00:20:28,978 --> 00:20:30,312
That's all it is.

429
00:20:30,855 --> 00:20:32,982
Half of my remaining lifespan?

430
00:20:33,691 --> 00:20:34,734
[Ryuk] Yeah.

431
00:20:35,151 --> 00:20:36,277
In other words,

432
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:39,697
if you are supposed to live
another 50 years, it'll be 25.

433
00:20:39,989 --> 00:20:42,324
If it was one more year, then six months.

434
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,743
I see.

435
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:46,746
And since you've made it clear
you're not on anyone's side,

436
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:47,913
and won't help me out,

437
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:50,624
you wouldn't just give me
the names of people I want to kill.

438
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:54,754
Basically, you're saying that I can't
simply borrow your powers.

439
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:56,672
I'd have to pay for them.

440
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:58,007
That's right.

441
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:01,385
It's a key part of the code
that all Shinigami are bound by.

442
00:21:02,303 --> 00:21:04,013
I'll say this once more.

443
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:06,599
Give me half your remaining lifespan,

444
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:09,268
and I'll give you the Shinigami Eyes.

445
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:10,686
If I agree…

446
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:14,315
I'll be able to know everyone's name
just by looking at them.

447
00:21:14,982 --> 00:21:16,150
If I had that power,

448
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,402
the Death Note
would only be easier to use.

449
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,572
So, what'll it be, Light?

450
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:22,948
Is it a deal?

451
00:21:27,630 --> 00:21:29,084
[music concludes]

452
00:21:29,163 --> 00:21:35,085
TO BE CONTINUED

453
00:21:40,439 --> 00:21:45,596
[theme song playing]

454
00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:48,479
[music concludes]
